    <article class="legal-article reveal">
      <header class="legal-header">
        <p class="eyebrow">Accessibility</p>
        <h1 class="headline-xl">For Everyone</h1>
        <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: December 2024</p>
      </header>

      <div class="legal-body">
        <h2>Our Commitment</h2>
        <p>
          Ferni is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. 
          We continually improve the user experience for everyone and apply relevant accessibility standards.
        </p>

        <h2>Accessibility Features</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Voice-First Interface:</strong> Ferni is designed primarily for voice interaction, making it accessible to users who cannot use traditional screen interfaces.</li>
          <li><strong>Phone Access:</strong> Call Ferni directly at {{ site.phone }}—no app download or visual interface required.</li>
          <li><strong>Screen Reader Support:</strong> Our web interface is designed to work with screen readers and assistive technologies.</li>
          <li><strong>Keyboard Navigation:</strong> Full keyboard navigation support throughout the web application.</li>
          <li><strong>High Contrast:</strong> Our design uses high-contrast colors that meet WCAG AA standards.</li>
          <li><strong>Resizable Text:</strong> All text can be resized up to 200% without loss of functionality.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Standards</h2>
        <p>
          We aim to conform to the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1, Level AA. 
          These guidelines explain how to make web content more accessible for people with disabilities.
        </p>

        <h2>Feedback</h2>
        <p>
          We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of Ferni. Please let us know if you encounter accessibility barriers:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email: <a href="mailto:accessibility@ferni.ai">accessibility@ferni.ai</a></li>
          <li>Phone: <a href="tel:{{ site.phoneRaw }}">{{ site.phone }}</a></li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We try to respond to accessibility feedback within 5 business days.
        </p>

        <h2>Continuous Improvement</h2>
        <p>
          We are always looking for ways to improve. If you have suggestions for how we can 
          improve accessibility, please contact us.
        </p>
      </div>
